# ✅ Git & GitHub Commands Cheat Sheet

## 🔧 Basic Setup

| Command                                  | What It Does           | Example                                         |
| ---------------------------------------- | ---------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- |
| `git config --global user.name "Name"`   | Sets your Git username | git config --global user.name "XYZ"        |
| `git config --global user.email "email"` | Sets your Git email    | git config --global user.email "<qa@email.com>" |

***

## 📥 Repository Setup

| Command                | What It Does                     | Example                                     |
| ---------------------- | -------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| `git clone <repo-url>` | Downloads repository from GitHub | git clone <https://github.com/user/app.git> |
| `cd folder-name`       | Moves into project directory     | cd app                                      |

***

## 🔍 Checking Status & Changes

| Command      | What It Does                           | Example    |
| ------------ | -------------------------------------- | ---------- |
| `git status` | Shows changed, staged, untracked files | git status |
| `git diff`   | Shows line-by-line changes             | git diff   |
| `git log`    | Shows commit history                   | git log    |

***

## ➕ Adding Files

| Command             | What It Does                  | Example         |
| ------------------- | ----------------------------- | --------------- |
| `git add file-name` | Adds specific file to staging | git add test.js |
| `git add .`         | Adds all files to staging     | git add .       |

***

## 💾 Commit Changes

| Command                   | What It Does          | Example                          |
| ------------------------- | --------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| `git commit -m "message"` | Saves changes locally | git commit -m "Added login test" |

***

## 🚀 Push & Pull

| Command                | What It Does                 | Example              |
| ---------------------- | ---------------------------- | -------------------- |
| `git push`             | Uploads code to GitHub       | git push             |
| `git push origin main` | Push to main branch          | git push origin main |
| `git pull`             | Gets latest code from GitHub | git pull             |
| `git pull origin main` | Pull from main branch        | git pull origin main |

***

## 🌿 Branch Management

| Command                       | What It Does           | Example                    |
| ----------------------------- | ---------------------- | -------------------------- |
| `git branch`                  | Lists all branches     | git branch                 |
| `git checkout -b branch-name` | Create + switch branch | git checkout -b login-test |
| `git checkout branch-name`    | Switch branch          | git checkout main          |
| `git branch -d branch-name`   | Deletes branch         | git branch -d login-test   |

***

## 🔀 Merge & Conflict Handling

| Command                   | What It Does                     | Example                           |
| ------------------------- | -------------------------------- | --------------------------------- |
| `git merge branch-name`   | Merge branch into current branch | git merge login-test              |
| `git status`              | Check conflicts                  | git status                        |
| `git add .`               | Mark conflict resolved           | git add .                         |
| `git commit -m "message"` | Complete merge                   | git commit -m "Resolved conflict" |

***

## 🧹 Remove / Clean Files

| Command            | What It Does                    | Example        |
| ------------------ | ------------------------------- | -------------- |
| `git rm file-name` | Deletes tracked file            | git rm test.js |
| `git clean -n`     | Preview untracked file deletion | git clean -n   |
| `git clean -f`     | Delete untracked files          | git clean -f   |

***

## 🔄 Undo / Reset

| Command                   | What It Does                 | Example                  |
| ------------------------- | ---------------------------- | ------------------------ |
| `git reset --soft HEAD~1` | Undo last commit (keep code) | git reset --soft HEAD\~1 |
| `git checkout -- file`    | Discard file changes         | git checkout -- test.js  |

***

## ✅ QA Daily Workflow (Quick Steps)

| Step            | Command                         |
| --------------- | ------------------------------- |
| Get latest code | git pull origin main            |
| Create branch   | git checkout -b TC-101          |
| Check changes   | git status                      |
| Add files       | git add .                       |
| Commit changes  | git commit -m "Test case added" |
| Push branch     | git push origin TC-101          |

